    <h2 id="petcare">Pet Care</h2>
    <p class="carep">
      Taking care of a pet is a big responsibility. It is important to make sure
      that your pet is healthy and happy. Here are some tips to help you take
      care of your pet:
    </p>
    <h3 class="care">Feeding</h3>
    <p class="carep">
      Make sure that your pet has a balanced diet. Different pets have different
      dietary needs. For example, dogs need a diet that is high in protein,
      while cats need a diet that is high in fat. It is important to feed your
      pet the right amount of food. Overfeeding can lead to obesity, while
      underfeeding can lead to malnutrition.
    </p>
    <h3 class="care">Exercise</h3>
    <p class="carep">
      Pets need regular exercise to stay healthy. Dogs need to be walked at
      least once a day. Cats need to be given toys to play with. Regular
      exercise can help prevent obesity and other health problems.
    </p>
    <h3 class="care">Grooming</h3>
    <p class="carep">
      Regular grooming is important for your pet's health. Dogs need to be
      bathed regularly to keep their skin and coat clean. Cats need to be
      brushed to prevent matting. It is important to keep your pet's nails
      trimmed to prevent them from becoming overgrown.
    </p>
    <h3 class="care">Veterinary Care</h3>
    <p class="carep">
      Regular visits to the veterinarian are important for your pet's health.
      Your pet needs to be vaccinated to prevent diseases. It is important to
      have your pet spayed or neutered to prevent overpopulation. Regular
      checkups can help detect health problems early.
    </p>
